# KMA OpenAPI data analysis

def average[T](ts: Iterable[T])(implicit num: Numeric[T]) = {
    num.toDouble( ts.sum ) / ts.size
}

val sky_km = kma_km.map(line => line.split(","))
                   .map(s => (s(0).substring(0,16)
                                  .replace("-", "")
                                  .replace(":", ""),
                              s(8).toDouble.toInt))

val cct = cas_nt.map(line => line.split(","))
                .map(arr => (arr(0).substring(0,13)
                                  .replace("-", "")
                                  .replace(":", "")
                                  +"00",
                             arr(34).toDouble))
                .groupByKey
                .map(s => (s._1, average(s._2)))
                .filter(s => s._2 < 10000)
                // .filter(s => s._1 )

val result_sky = sky_km.collect.mkString(", ")
val result_cct = cct.collect.mkString(", ")

paragraphs.title: Sun Rise Set RDD
paragraphs.text:
val sunriseset = sun.map(s => s.split(','))
                    .map(s => (s(0),
                               s(1).substring(0,5),
                               s(2).substring(0,5))
                        )
                    .filter(_._1 > "2017-04-01")
                    .collect

def get_sunriseset_time(day: String) = {
    val e = sunriseset.filter(_._1 == day)(0)
    Map("rise" -> e._2, "set" -> e._3)
}

val date = "2018-02-08"
val srs = get_sunriseset_time(date)

%md
# Analysis for Getting Correlation Between SKY and SWR

val swr = cas_nt.map(line => line.split(","))
                .map(arr => (arr(0).substring(0,13)
                                  .replace("-", "")
                                  .replace(":", "")
                                  +"00",
                             arr(57).toDouble
                             ))
                .filter(t => t._2 < 100)
                .filter(t => t._2 > 0)
                .groupByKey
                .map(s => (s._1, average(s._2)))
                .filter(s => s._2 < 10000)
                // .filter(s => s._1 )

val rdd_skyswr = sky_km.join(swr)
                       .map(s => (s._1.split()(0),      //date
                                      (s._1.split()(1), //hour
                                          (s._2._1,     //sky
                                          s._2._2)      //swr
                                      )
                                  ))
                       .groupByKey
                       .

val rdd_skyswr2 = sky_km.join(swr)
                       .map(s => (s._1.split()(0),
                                  s._1.split()(1),
                                  s._2._1,
                                  s._2._2))

val df_sky_swr = rdd_skyswr2.toDF("date", "hour", "sky", "swr")
df_sky_swr.createOrReplaceTempView("skyswr")

%sql
select * from skyswr
-- where datehour between '20180101 0000' and '20180331 2400'
order by date asc

paragraphs.title: SWR 2nd arrange - 180405
paragraphs.text:
val srs = get_sunriseset_time("2018-02-08")
val swr_a = cas_nt.map(line => line.split(","))
                  .map(arr => (arr(0).substring(0,10),//yyyy-mm-dd
                               (arr(0).substring(11,16),//hh:mm
                                arr(57).toDouble)   //idx57 = swr
                              )
                      )
                  .filter(_._2._2 > 0)
                  .filter(_._2._2 < 100)
                  .groupByKey
                  .filter(_._1 == "2018-02-08")
                  .map(_._2)
                  .collect()(0)
                  .toList
                  .filter(_._1 >= srs("rise"))
                  .filter(_._1 <= srs("set"))
                  .map(t => (t._1.split(":")(0), t._2))

paragraphs.title: Getting SWR method - 180406
paragraphs.text:
def average[T](ts: Iterable[T])(implicit num: Numeric[T]) = {
    num.toDouble( ts.sum ) / ts.size
}


//date format : yyyy-mm-dd
def daily_swr(date: String):List[(Int, Double)] = {
    val srs = get_sunriseset_time(date)
    
    val swr_a = cas_nt.map(line => line.split(","))
                      .map(arr => (arr(0).substring(0,10),//yyyy-mm-dd
                                   (arr(0).substring(11,16),//hh:mm
                                    arr(57).toDouble)   //idx57 = swr
                                  )
                          )
                      .filter(_._2._2 > 0)
                      .filter(_._2._2 < 100)
                      .groupByKey
                      .filter(_._1 == date)        //pick one day data
                      .map(_._2)
                      .collect()(0)
                      .toList                       //make List
                      .filter(_._1 >= srs("rise"))
                      .filter(_._1 <= srs("set"))
                      .map(t => (t._1.split(":")(0).toInt, t._2))
                      
    return swr_a
}
